Ad Text:
At TechnologyOne, we are dedicated to transforming the way organisations manage their Payroll functions through innovative software solutions. Our commitment to delivering exceptional value to our clients drives us to continuously improve and expand our offerings. Join us in shaping the future of Payroll technology.

Reimagine Payroll. Drive Innovation. Reduce Risk.

Step into a pivotal role shaping the future of payroll As a Senior Business Analyst at TechnologyOne, you'll deliver on the strategic direction of a modern, cloud-native platform that's transforming how councils and universities manage their workforce.

This is about creating intelligent, AI-driven payroll automation that replaces outdated, error-prone processes. You'll work at the forefront of innovation, embedding regulatory intelligence, streamlining compliance, and delivering frictionless payroll operations at scale.

If you're currently navigating legacy systems, consultancy roadmaps, or patchwork automation - this is your chance to drive real change, reduce payroll risk, and build a product that's redefining trust in public sector payroll.

Key Responsibilities:

Be a thought leader in the payroll domain, with a strong emphasis on regulatory impacts, change, and market trends affecting Local Government and/or Education sectors.
Actively engage with customers, consulting, sales and support to gather market intelligence and customer feedback to inform global product design.
Join customer forums and industry events, contributing thought leadership and gathering direct insights Payroll Professionals to inform the product roadmap in Local Government and Education.
Work across time zones to ensure regional priorities are effectively scoped and delivered.
Undertake internal change activities to support new capabilities - enabling consulting, presales, and customer success teams with product awareness and knowledge.
Drive external product awareness with customers and industry partners, ensuring clear communication of roadmap direction and product enhancement timelines.


What We're Looking For...

Understanding of Payroll complexity in Local Government, and/or Higher Education institutions.
Proven ability to engage with customers to gather requirements, deliver presentations and manage customer expectations.
Experience and understanding of regional data privacy requirements for management of people data.
A focus on delivering customer value.
A passion for technology and a drive to improve user experiences, with enthusiasm for defining and delivering Artificial Intelligence automation for Payroll processes.



Why Join us?

Help us redefine payroll software for Local Government and Education.

We’re recruiting a Senior Data Scientist to join a large, consumer-focused organisation with 10+ years of transactional data and a major data platform transformation underway. This is a hands-on role in a mature environment where you will work on the design, build, refresh, and validation of predictive models that directly inform commercial decisions across customer acquisition, retention, cross-sell, and revenue growth.

What You’ll Be Doing

Identify and leverage new data sources as platforms evolve
Support experimentation, testing, and uplift of decision accuracy
Contribute to future capability uplift as the data science function grows

5+ years’ hands-on data science experience in industry (not academia)

Competitive package and benefits on offer. This is a hybrid role, two days working from office a week.

How to Apply

Apply via Seek or contact Jelissa Taylor for a confidential discussion.

UGL Utilities Operations & Maintenance business is a trusted provider of essential services across power, water, and gas sectors. With a strong reputation and long-standing contracts in power distribution, transmission, and water operations and maintenance, we are poised for significant growth.


About the role

The Systems & Improvement Lead plays a key role in ensuring operational efficiency across UGL Services by supporting, enhancing, and deploying digital and business systems. The role gathers stakeholder requirements, documents processes, manages system rollout projects, and provides ongoing support to operational teams. It contributes to continuous improvement initiatives that enable safer, better, faster, and more efficient ways of working across contracts.

This position will be based at our North Sydney office.

Key responsibilities

Document business processes and system workflows using clear process maps.

Maintain accurate and current documentation for operational systems.

Project manage the rollout of digital systems, including planning, design, development, testing, deployment,and handover to operations.

Work collaboratively with IT, Operations, and program stakeholders to ensure successful delivery within agreed timelines and budget constraints.

Support change management activities, including communications, training, and adoption planning.

Provide user support, troubleshooting, and system guidance to operational teams.

Coordinate updates, enhancements, and configuration changes in line with business needs.

Monitor system performance and proactively identify improvement opportunities.

Identify and document improvement opportunities across systems, workflows, and operational processes.

Support teams in applying improved ways of working that deliver measurable operational value.

Contribute to national or contract-level improvement initiatives as required.

Lead or support system related components of new contract mobilisations, ensuring readiness of digital tools, data, and processes.

Liaise with internal and external stakeholders to ensure smooth transition into operations.

About You

Minimum 5 years in a systems, process improvement, or similar role

Experience within construction, utilities, services, or project‑based environments

Proficiency with MS Office, SharePoint, Teams, Power BI, Power Apps, Power Automate, and Visio.

Experience with SAP, SAP Field Service Management (FSM), and Cognito Forms (desirable).

Ad Text:
We've been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with 120,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you'll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you'll also get to see your impact.

 

About the team

 

As the way Australians shop continues to evolve, our Data and AI Team keep Coles at the forefront of modern retail. We combine data, artificial intelligence, and applied engineering to reimagine how our stores, supply chain, and digital channels operate — creating smarter, more connected, and seamless experiences for our customers and team members.

 

Operating as a centralised development and enablement function within Coles Technology, the team unites product, engineering, and platform capabilities to deliver the intelligence layer of the enterprise. We serve every part of Coles — from computer vision applications that enhance in-store experiences and reduce loss, to forecasting, optimisation, and decision-support solutions that drive efficiency, accuracy, and agility across our supply chain, retail operations, and corporate functions.

 

The scale and impact of this work are significant. Coles serves millions of customers each week across more than a thousand stores nationwide, and our AI and data capabilities provide the intelligence that underpins how we plan, move, sell, and serve. By combining deep data capability with applied AI and modern engineering, we’re enabling Coles to become a truly AI-enabled enterprise, transforming how we operate and how Australia shops every day.



About the role

 

As Senior Platform Manager for Data and Visualisation, your primary function will be to define and lead the enterprise data and visualisation platform strategy whilst overseeing delivery of scalable, secure, and governed data platform capabilities.

 

Key responsibilities will include

 

Drive implementation of modern cloud-native data architecture (Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, etc.)
Ensure platform reliability, scalability, and compliance with SLA commitments
Lead enterprise-wide visualisation strategy (Power BI, Tableau, etc.)
Champion self-service analytics and consistent data storytelling
Provide functional leadership to Platform and Governance Managers
Embed "governance by design" into platform engineering
Act as key interface between business teams and technology delivery squads
Ensure alignment with enterprise data, security, and AI/ML platform strategies
Evaluate, select and integrate modern data tools and technologies
Oversee CI/CD, DevOps and automation practices for data pipelines and dashboards
Ensure strong data lifecycle management across ingestion, storage, access, and usage

 

 

About You and Your Skills

 

10+ years in data platform, analytics or architecture roles
5+ years in senior data platform or engineering leadership
Proven delivery of enterprise-scale data and BI platforms (cloud/on-prem)
Experience managing cross-functional teams including engineers, governance, and DevOps
Strong background in visualisation tools (Power BI, MicroStrategy)
Hands-on expertise in cloud platforms (Azure), Snowflake, Databricks, Oracle
Experience building CI/CD pipelines for data and dashboard deployments
Proven data governance, metadata, and compliance expertise
Skilled in stakeholder management across business and technology functions
Proficient in SQL and programming languages (Python, Scala, Java)
Familiar with Agile, product delivery models, and hybrid team structures

 

Skills and Qualifications

 

Deep expertise in modern data platforms, BI architecture, and visualisation tooling
Strong knowledge of distributed systems (Spark, Kafka) and orchestration tools (Control M, ADF, Airflow)
Ability to influence and align senior stakeholders across tech and business
Excellent communication and data storytelling skills
Knowledge of data security, access control, and regulatory compliance
Strong understanding of DevOps for data engineering

 

Education

Bachelor's or Master's Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, or a related field.

 

Please note that we are seeking a candidate with deep experience in data platforms and proven people‑leadership capabilities, including leading leaders. Strong communication skills are also essential.

 



What’s in it for you?

 

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

 

About the recruitment process

 

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

 

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Randstad is partnering with a major Federal Government Body to recruit a strategic EL1 Research & Program Manager.

This isn't just a data role; it is a pivotal position within the Market Research Unit (MRU). You will be responsible for providing the evidence base that drives national public health behavior change campaigns. You will work where data meets creativity, ensuring every government message is underpinned by robust behavioral insights.

Position Overview

Pay Rate: $85 - $105 per hour + super

Location: Hybrid (Sydney or Canberra)

Contract Length: 6 months

The Campaign & Research Cycle

Campaign Strategy & Design: Manage behavioral research projects that define target audiences and inform the strategic direction of public health campaigns.

Influence & Communication: Ability to "tell the story" of the data, influencing senior stakeholders and the Director of the MRU with high-level reports and infographics.
How to Apply

If you have a background in market research, behavioral economics, or evidence-based communications, we encourage you to apply.

At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

Business Analyst | Federal Government

About the Role We are seeking an experienced Business Analyst to provide high-level analytical and project support within a prominent Federal Government Department. This role is responsible for the oversight and enhancement of information systems used to support critical departmental functions both within Australia and across our global network.

The successful candidate will act as a primary link between business units and technical teams, translating strategic organisational needs into robust technical requirements.

Key Responsibilities

Requirement Lifecycle Management: Engage with diverse stakeholders to gather, refine, and document user requirements using industry-standard techniques (workshops, interviews, use cases, and workflow analysis).

Technical Translation: Analyse complex system requirements and communicate technical specifications effectively to both developers and non-technical business users.

Project Documentation: Produce high-quality project artefacts, including business cases, risk management plans, and detailed ICT system reports.

Stakeholder Engagement: Build and maintain productive, collaborative relationships with internal departmental branches and external service providers.

System Design & Implementation: Assist in the delivery of ICT projects by providing expertise in system design, specification, and business process mapping.

Configuration & Support: Undertake ongoing system administration and liaise with vendors to configure platforms to meet specific business requirements.

Change Management: Lead the development of standard operating procedures (SOPs), training materials, and "helpcard" resources to support the optimisation and adoption of new business processes.

Continuous Improvement: Proactively identify opportunities to improve business processes and enhance system functionality.

Selection Criteria (Skills & Experience)

Government ICT Experience: Proven experience as a Business Analyst on significant ICT projects, preferably within an Australian Federal Government environment.

Analytical Rigour: Demonstrated ability to define clear, measurable acceptance criteria to ensure technical solutions are fit for purpose and meet business needs.

Communication Excellence: High-level verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to negotiate and influence outcomes across all levels of a Department.

Initiative & Autonomy: A self-starter with the ability to work independently, manage competing priorities, and prioritise results under tight deadlines.

Discretion & Integrity: A proven ability to maintain strict confidentiality and exercise sound judgement when handling sensitive or classified information.

Eligibility & Requirements

Citizenship: Candidates must be Australian Citizens to be eligible for this role.

Security Clearance: Applicants must currently hold NV1, or NV2 security clearance (as required by the Department).

A key role driving business efficiency and cost performance across a dynamic mining operation

About the Opportunity


An opportunity has arisen for a Senior Business Analyst to join our 29Metals team in Western Australia.


Reporting to the Commercial Manager, you will focus on supporting cost and capital reporting, driving variance analysis, and partnering with the business to improve efficiency. You will be playing a key role in embedding a culture of continuous improvement.


Key responsibilities will include:
Gather and document detailed business requirements.
Analyse and map current state processes to identify gaps and opportunities.
Define and document reporting requirements, KPIs, and dashboards across transformation projects and operational teams.
Develop models to support financing and investment decisions
Collaborate with management to ensure milestones are achieved
Support governance with requirements updates and data readiness reporting
About You


Our ideal candidate is a proactive finance professional with strong skills in budgeting, reporting, compliance, and process improvement, and is capable of driving efficiency across the business.


Other key skills, experience, and qualifications: 
Relevant tertiary qualification in Finance or Accounting
Minimum 4 years’ experience in Senior Business Analysis experience or Big 4 firm
Proven experience building and developing financial models
Strong knowledge of accounting standards and regulatory compliance
Demonstrated ability to conduct in-depth analysis of business needs
Expertise in business and data analysis methodologies, techniques, tools, and templates, including process re-engineering, optimisation and automation
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, able to convey information clearly to technical and non-technical stakeholders
About 29Metals and Golden Grove


29Metals is an ASX-listed mining company producing copper and other base and precious metals critical to the global energy transition. Headquartered in Melbourne, we also have support offices in Perth and Brisbane.


We operate two long-life assets: Golden Grove in Western Australia and Capricorn Copper in Queensland, along with a portfolio of exploration interests, including a strategic tenement package and a project in Redhill, Chile.


Golden Grove is a high-grade underground mining operation producing copper, zinc, and precious metals. With a mine life exceeding 10 years, it has strong potential for further extension. The site is currently undergoing an expansion, including the development of a new mine, the extension of existing operations, and major infrastructure upgrades.

Full-time permanent position with flexible working arrangements

Proven experience working across agile, waterfall, or hybrid delivery environments

Strong stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence and engage at all levels, including senior leaders

Experience coaching or leading Business Analysts

Strong data analysis skills, including working with complex datasets and assessing data quality

Exceptional analytical thinking and attention to detail

About us

We’re proud to be one of South Australia’s most iconic brands, trusted by members for more than 120 years. SA born-and-bred, RAA might be best known for our road service and insurance products, but we’re excited to be continuously diversifying to better help our members and community.

Our goal? To make life better for South Australians. That’s why we’re proud to offer a range of services to our 820,000+ members, including travel, energy, solar and battery, electric vehicle charging, our RAA Rewards program and more. With motoring still a priority, we’re just as passionate as we were in 1903 about road safety, advocating for a safer SA into the future.

We’re also one of the state’s largest employers, with more than 1100 employees working across our local sites at Mile End, RAA Place (CBD) and Adelaide Airport and our many retail and travel shops. With new office spaces in the city and city fringe in the works, and a buzzing people-first culture, we’re proud to be the State’s #1 Employer Brand.

Free RAA premium road service

Wellbeing facilities and Corporate Health Insurance Plan

Ad Text:
Position overview

2-Year Maximum-Term Contract, Full-Time opportunity

About us
We're on a mission to create a brighter future, where you can be a change maker at the actual source. We're one of Australia's largest water utilities with over 30% of Victoria's population relying on us for their essential water and sanitation services.

Our award-winning culture fosters an inclusive, collaborative, and flexible environment that enables our people to thrive. Here, you'll be inspired and challenged to grow alongside us.

The Role
The Technical Lead will drive the design, delivery, and evolution of YVW's next-generation data platform, with end-to-end accountability for migrating our legacy finance system to modern platforms to underpin improved financial integrity, regulatory confidence, operational insight and decision-making. You will lead all phases of data ingestion, complex transformations, and enhancements, while also redesigning and optimising existing Enterprise, Data and Analytics (EDA) platform solutions to deliver scalable, automated, and high-performance data pipelines.

Reporting directly to the Head of Data & Analytics, you will provide hands-on technical leadership across multi-disciplinary teams and contractors, ensuring solutions are delivered on time, to specification, and aligned to enterprise architecture and governance standards. This is a highly visible and strategic role, combining deep technical expertise, data engineering mastery, scripting proficiency, and delivery leadership with the ability to influence and guide senior stakeholders and vendor partners.

You will also be responsible for reverse engineering existing ETL jobs, stored procedures, and reporting logic, modernising and optimising them for maintainability, performance, and automation, ensuring the platform delivers trusted, accurate, and timely reporting and analytics.

Working closely with Project Managers, data engineers, delivery leads, analysts, architects, vendors, and business stakeholders, you will drive delivery excellence across all initiatives. This role is ideal for an experienced technical leader who thrives in complex, high-impact environments and is motivated by shaping the future of enterprise data at scale.

Your key responsibilities

Lead the end-to-end delivery of data migration, data engineering, and transformation initiatives across Finance domains (General Ledger, Accounts Payable/Receivable, Asset Accounting, Payroll, Procurement, Treasury) on Azure and Databricks, ensuring automation, scalability, reliability, and high data quality.
Own data migration strategy, designs, and execution, including planning, remediation, and data quality validation throughout all phases of the migration.
Provide hands-on technical leadership across multi-disciplinary teams and contractors, guiding delivery of migration, engineering, analytics, and EDA optimisation initiatives.
Redesign, refactor, and optimise existing data pipelines, transformations, and models on the EDA platform to improve performance, maintainability, and alignment with target architecture.
Assess current EDA solutions and identify opportunities to simplify logic, remove duplication, and retire technical debt.
Architect, develop, and optimise scalable data pipelines, lakehouse architectures, and reusable data products.
Lead complex legacy-to-cloud data migrations, including reverse engineering ETL jobs, stored procedures, and reporting logic, and re-engineering them for performance, automation, and maintainability.
Design and implement enterprise-grade data models and semantic layers to support analytics, operational reporting, and future machine learning use cases.
Ensure migrated and redesigned data assets are fully reconciled, validated, and fit for business consumption.
Enable self-service analytics through well-curated, trusted datasets and Power BI semantic models.
Implement CI/CD and DevOps practices to automate data ingestion, transformation, testing, and deployment.
Enforce data governance, quality, security, and documentation standards across the data platform.
Conduct data discovery and profiling of legacy and source systems to identify quality issues, gaps, risks, and ownership responsibilities.
Develop and maintain source-to-target data mappings and support ETL processes using Databricks, SQL, and related technologies.
Execute mock migrations, reconciliations, and validations across Dev, SIT, and UAT environments, documenting and resolving defects.
Collaborate with business SMEs, analysts, and product owners to translate requirements into scalable, sustainable solutions.
Provide technical oversight, assurance, and quality review of vendor-delivered solutions.
Support Agile delivery, including estimation, planning, and management of technical dependencies.
Mentor and coach data engineers and analysts, driving capability uplift, standards adoption, and delivery maturity.
Drive continuous improvement across migration, data engineering, analytics, and EDA optimisation practices.

What we're looking for

Proven experience as a Tech Lead or Lead Data Engineer in complex enterprise environments.
Delivering large-scale data migration projects, ideally within Finance systems
Strong hands‑on expertise in data engineering, including ETL/ELT design, data modelling, and integration patterns.
Demonstrated experience leading and delivering end‑to‑end data migration programs.
Strong capability in reverse engineering undocumented or poorly documented legacy data solutions.
Advanced Power BI experience, including semantic modelling, DAX, performance optimisation, and governance.
Deep hands‑on experience with Microsoft Azure data services (e.g. Azure Data Lake, Data Factory, Azure SQL/Synapse, Databricks).
Strong understanding of lakehouse architectures, scalable data pipelines, and modern analytics platforms.
Experience implementing DevOps, CI/CD, and automation for data workloads.
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills, with the ability to translate technical concepts for non‑technical audiences.
Experience working in Agile, cross‑functional delivery environments.
Demonstrated ability to manage multiple priorities under pressure, with excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.

Integration requirements

Lynch Group is recruiting a hands-on SAP Integration Technical Lead to own the design, delivery and operational stability of integrations for our SAP S/4HANA Public Cloud landscape. ·         Conduct scenario, sensitivity and risk‑adjusted analyses

·         Support due diligence, transaction execution and post‑acquisition integration

·         Develop standardised valuation frameworks across IMDEX

·         Prepare decision‑ready valuation reports for Senior Management and the Board

·         Collaborate with Finance, Legal and commercial teams to ensure strong governance and optimal deal structures




What You’ll Bring

If you’re a valuation expert who thrives in dynamic environments and wants to be part of a global team shaping the future of mining technology, this could be your next move.

·         Excellent communication, presentation and stakeholder‑management skills

The role of Data Engineer will be a key contributor to the migration of our client's reporting platform, focusing on back-end systems and data infrastructure. This role is responsible for ensuring the smooth integration and processing of large-scale data, building robust data pipelines, and creating scalable data products to support multiple applications across the company. The Data Engineer will collaborate with various departments to implement and maintain high-performance data systems that empower business users with actionable insights. Responsibilities also include optimizing data workflows, driving innovation in data engineering processes, and ensuring data integrity throughout the platform migration.




Main responsibilities:

· Collaboration: Partner with cross-functional teams to understand their data needs and design solutions that streamline data flows and integration across multiple applications.

· Semantic Model & KPI Definitions: Build and maintain a comprehensive semantic model, working closely with stakeholders to define and standardize KPIs that align with business objectives and reporting requirements.

· Platform Migration: help with back-end migration efforts, ensuring that all data pipelines, storage solutions, and processing systems are transitioned efficiently and without disruption to business operations.

· Data Pipeline Development: Design, build, and maintain scalable and efficient data pipelines that ensure accurate and timely data delivery to support business intelligence tools and applications.

· System Optimization: Continuously optimize and monitor back-end systems, databases, and data workflows to maintain high performance and cost-efficiency.

· Data Integration: Ensure seamless integration of data from various sources into centralized platforms, enabling comprehensive reporting and analysis capabilities.

· Problem-Solving: Leverage data engineering expertise to troubleshoot issues, optimize performance, and solve complex challenges related to data storage, processing, and accessibility.

· Innovation & Collaboration: Work closely with the Data & IT teams to explore new technologies and methodologies, driving innovation in the company's data engineering practices and supporting evolving business needs.




Requirements:

Must have

University Degree (Data Engineering, Information Systems, or a related field)

3+ years in a data engineering or similar role, with demonstrated success in supporting data transformation and migration projects, ideally from legacy systems to modern data platforms

Proven track record in supporting data transformation projects, nice to have would be migrating from legacy systems to modern BI tools like Power BI

Technical Skills:

Data Transformation: Strong experience in ETL/ELT processes, data modeling, and reporting in Microsoft environment (SSIS, Azure DataFactory, Synapse, Fabric)

Power BI Semantic Model: Proven ability to create and maintain a comprehensive analytical data models, specifically in Power BI and/or Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services (SSAS), including KPI definitions and metric standardization to meet reporting requirements

SQL Proficiency: Proficient in SQL (any dialect) for data manipulation, transformation, and analysis.

DAX Proficiency: Proficient in DAX language for Analysis Services/Power BI.

Data Pipelines: Experience building and optimizing data pipelines for large-scale data processing.

Cloud Experience: Familiarity with cloud environments such as Azure, with a focus on tools like Synapse Analytics

Ability to analyze both structured and unstructured data, with a proactive approach to identifying and solving data issues

Effective communication skills to collaborate with stakeholders across departments, strong problem-solving abilities, and a commitment to data quality and accuracy

English at business level

Visa sponsorship is available for candidates without existing Australian work rights

Nice to have

· Experience with SSRS and SSIS, or similar reporting and integration tools

· Hands-on experience with BI tools like Power BI, with a strong understanding of KPI definitions and dashboard creation

Optus is an Australian telecommunications company, delivering more than 11 million services to our customers every day across mobile, broadband, and digital solutions.

Join our Billing & Credit team within Group Finance, where we ensure customers across all Optus segments experience simple, accurate and secure billing and payments. As a key contributor to this high‑performing function, you'll help champion our customers through better onboarding, clear billing experiences and strong financial controls.

As the Senior Portfolio Analyst, you'll use your analytical expertise to build insightful reporting, drive automation & self-serve, , improve credit risk oversight, and support risk‑aware decision‑making. You'll analyse complex data, develop dashboards and KPIs, streamline processes, and collaborate across teams to deliver actionable insights that enhance performance, reduce risk and improve outcomes for both customers and the business.

What you'll be doing

Lead the creation and automation of high‑quality reporting and analytics solutions for to monitor controls across the E2E credit management & credit lifecycle across all channels and all systems to support adherence to credit risk internal policies, regulatory requirement, compliance & governance requirements, and to manage overall credit risk performance.
Deliver actionable insights by analysing trends, building forecasting models and translating complex performance data into clear opportunities that drive improved business outcomes.
Partner with stakeholders by leading performance discussions, managing deliverables, and translating complex analytical and financial insights into clear, actionable business impacts.
Collaborate across Optus to align reporting solutions with enterprise data standards, while sharing expertise and best practices to uplift capability across teams.
Ensure data accuracy and governance by maintaining a clean reporting catalogue, data library, standard operating procedures, enforcing consistent definitions and methods, and building strong data models.

What makes you perfect for the role?

Degree in business, finance, statistics or related field, with telco experience valued.
5+ years in data analytics with strong skills in data modelling, integration, visualisation and advanced SQL across large datasets.
Proficient with BI tools (Tableau, Cognos, Alteryx), advanced Excel/VBA, and experienced in data quality, lineage and ETL processes.
Solid background in credit risk, billing or financial reporting, with the ability to translate policy and regulatory requirements into actionable, compliant insights.
High proficiency in Excel (financial analysis and modelling), PowerPoint, and complex database work.
Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to simplify complex insights for senior stakeholders.

Are you ready to shape the future of data architecture and help build a modern, scalable, and insights-driven enterprise?

We’re seeking an experienced Senior Data Architect to lead the design and delivery of next-generation data solutions — from data lakes and integration frameworks to advanced analytics platforms.

As the Senior Data Architect, you’ll play a key role in defining and delivering the organisation’s enterprise data architecture. In addition, you’ll ensure data is structured, governed, and leveraged effectively to support operational and strategic decision-making.

You’ll provide architectural leadership across integration, data warehousing, analytics, and governance while fostering collaboration between business units, technical teams, and senior leadership.

Key Responsibilities of the Senior Data Architect will include:
Develop and maintain enterprise-wide data architecture strategies, ensuring scalability, security, and alignment with business goals.

About the Company 

Ahrens is a fifth-generation, Australian family-owned company, with over 120 years’ experience in delivering a wide range of high-quality and cost-effective products and projects across Australia, with footprints overseas.  

Our growth has culminated in the business we are today: a full Construction, Engineering, Mining & Industrial Services, Sheds & Silos and Water Storage company which provides complete turnkey project solutions, supported by our 26 divisions.  

As we continue to evolve, so does our need to heavily invest in our people and facilities for continued success.  

With close to 2,000 employees Australia-wide, we foster a positive and supportive team culture which embraces diversity and innovation, while aligning with our core values of commitment, integrity and safety. In return, we reward those who passionately work with us towards our vision.  

About the Role 

Our IT team is growing, and we’re recruiting multiple Business Analysts including this Senior IT Business Analyst role. The Senior IT Business Analyst drives enterprise-wide change across people, processes, and technology, with a strong focus on technology enabled initiatives and application optimisation.

The role combines senior level business analysis with hands on responsibility for the configuration, support, and continuous improvement of core business systems. Working across agile, waterfall, and hybrid delivery models, the role partners with business and technical teams to translate requirements into secure, practical solutions, while ensuring system reliability and supporting continuous improvement and successful transformation outcomes.

This role will be working across the Ahrens Group and specifically working on projects at our Vaughan Constructions division. 

Skills and Experience 

The successful candidate must have tertiary qualifications in ICT related disciplines and proven experience in a similar role, ideally from a fast paced and busy IT support environment.

Ahrens is seeking a dynamic team player with strong written and verbal communication skills, who can build and maintain relationships with a range of stakeholders at different levels across the business.

This role requires excellent problem-solving skills, as well as strong experience with systems implementation and support. Candidates who are familiar and experienced with a broad portfolio of business applications are highly desirable for this role. 

Benefits 

Employee Assistance Program, supporting you and your family’s health & wellbeing 

Discounts to some of Australia’s leading corporate partners in private health insurance, gyms, travel, clothing, vehicles and more 

Generous paid parental leave entitlements to support you and your family 

Annual Employee Donation Scheme to support a charity/cause of your choice 

Family, social and team building events including Friday afternoon team bonding 

Opportunities for career progression
